	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64505089"><p>Will we eventually be able to convert the entire economy over to ad serving? I mean, clearly it's a money maker. Everybody wants a piece.</p><p>I'm a little baffled how advertising can be such a money maker. We all hate ads. We're all annoyed to no end by them. Yet businesses leap at the opportunity to create yet more ads. I just have trouble wrapping my head around how annoying the shit out of people = give us money. You wouldn't pay a dude to run around the office screaming in people's faces that they need to buy more $product_of_the_day, yet we accept that same action nearly everywhere we seek entertainment or information. And we literally pay for it. WTF?</p></div>
